member.summary:
            Called on all content with this interface before , and after .

This is where you copy data from the main world to a subworld, via .
            SubworldSystem.CopyWorldData(nameof(DownedSystem.downedBoss), DownedSystem.downedBoss);

            Called on all content with this interface before a subworld generates, or after a subworld loads from file.

This is where you read data copied from the main world to a subworld, via .
            DownedSystem.downedBoss = SubworldSystem.ReadCopiedWorldData<bool>(nameof(DownedSystem.downedBoss));

            Called on all subworlds before , and after .

This is where you copy data from the main world to the subworld, via .
            SubworldSystem.CopyWorldData(nameof(DownedSystem.downedBoss), DownedSystem.downedBoss);

            Called before .

This is where you copy data from the subworld to another world, via .
            SubworldSystem.CopyWorldData(nameof(DownedSystem.downedBoss), DownedSystem.downedBoss);

            Called on all subworlds before one generates, or after one loads from file.

This is where you read data copied from the main world to the subworld, via .
            DownedSystem.downedBoss = SubworldSystem.ReadCopiedWorldData<bool>(nameof(DownedSystem.downedBoss));

            Called while leaving the subworld, either before a different world generates, or after a different world loads from file.

This is where you read data copied from the subworld to another world, via .
            DownedSystem.downedBoss = SubworldSystem.ReadCopiedWorldData<bool>(nameof(DownedSystem.downedBoss));

Corrects zoom and clears the screen, then calls DrawMenu and draws the cursor.

PlayerInput.SetZoom_UI();
Main.instance.GraphicsDevice.Clear(Color.Black);
Main.spriteBatch.Begin(SpriteSortMode.Deferred, BlendState.AlphaBlend, SamplerState.LinearClamp, DepthStencilState.None, Main.Rasterizer, null, Main.UIScaleMatrix);
DrawMenu(gameTime);
Main.DrawCursor(Main.DrawThickCursor());
Main.spriteBatch.End();

Tries to get the index of the subworld with the specified ID.
Typically used for .
Returns if the subworld couldn't be found. public override int ReturnDestination => SubworldSystem.GetIndex("MyMod/MySubworld");

Can only be called in or !
Stores data to be transferred between worlds under the specified key, if that key is not already in use.
Naming the key after the variable pointing to the data is highly recommended to avoid redundant copying. This can be done automatically with nameof(). SubworldSystem.CopyWorldData(nameof(DownedSystem.downedBoss), DownedSystem.downedBoss);

            Can only be called in  or !

Reads data copied from another world stored under the specified key.
            DownedSystem.downedBoss = SubworldSystem.ReadCopiedWorldData<bool>(nameof(DownedSystem.downedBoss));
